President Obama released a statement expressing his grief over the passing of Beau Biden, who was a friend of the Obamas. Beau Biden, the son of Vice President Joe Biden, was described as a good, big-hearted, devoutly Catholic man who made a difference in the lives of others. The statement highlighted the importance of family to Beau and his father, Joe Biden, who is known for his strength and love for his family. The Bidens have a large extended family and support system, and the White House also considers them part of their own family. The statement ended with a quote from poet William Butler Yeats, emphasizing Beau Biden's belief in the best of people and calling for others to follow his example. The Obamas offered their prayers for Beau and his family.